==English==

===Noun===
'''plumbing''' (''[[uncountable]]'')

#The [[pipe]]s, together with the [[joint]]s, [[tank]]s, [[stopcock]]s, [[tap]]s and other [[fixture]]s of a [[water]], [[gas]] or [[sewage]] [[system]] in a [[house]] or other [[building]].
#The [[trade]] or [[occupation]] of a [[plumber]].
#(''informal'') A system of [[vessel]]s or [[duct]]s in the [[human]] [[body]], especially the [[genitourinary]] system.
#:''My plumbing was playing up, so I had to see the doctor.''

====Synonyms====
*(''genitourinary system''): [[waterworks]] (''informal'')

